lead_paragraph: Lorena Ochoa moved into position to wrap up the L.P.G.A. Tour player of the year race and win her sixth title of the year, shooting a 9-under 63 to take a five-stroke lead at the L.P.G.A. Tournament of Champions in Mobile, Ala. With a victory today, Ochoa, 24, will become the first player other than Annika Sorenstam or Karrie Webb to be named player of the year since 1996.
